Q2

“ax + by + cz = 0” represents a plane in 3D space. Generate many points on the plane and draw them in 3D. Also indicate the direction of a vector (a,b,c) in the drawing.

Q2-1

“ax + by + cz = 0” represents a plane in 3D space. Generate many points on the plane and draw them in 3D.

Q2-2

Also indicate the direction of a vector (a,b,c) in the drawing.

参考http://www.sthda.com/english/wiki/impressive-package-for-3d-and-4d-graph-r-software-and-data-visualization　#scatter3D,arrows3D失敗

参考https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36920713/draw-arrows-in-3d-based-on-package-rgl　こちらで

d <- 1
n <- 10000
a <- rnorm(1) #ランダムのa
b <- rnorm(1) #ランダムのb
c <- rnorm(1) #ランダムのc
x <- matrix(rnorm(d*n),ncol=d) #ランダムで多数のx
y <- matrix(rnorm(d*n),ncol=d) #ランダムで多数のy
z <- y %*% (-a) / c + x %*% (-b) / c 
print(c(a,b,c))
## [1]  1.4781089 -2.1616049  0.1233168
library(rgl)
plot3d(x,y,z) 
arrow3d(c(0, 0, 0), c(a, b, c), type = "extrusion", col = "red")　#Q2-2
